events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Milwaukee Bucks

headlines.description: — Damian Lillard acknowledged his first game against his former team felt a little bit different at first.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks overcome 26-point deficit to beat Trail Blazers in Lillard's 1st game against former team

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 34 points, Jaylen Brown had 21 and the injury-depleted NBA-best Boston Celtics beat the Atlanta Hawks 113-103 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum scores 34, Jaylen Brown 21 in Celtics' 113-103 win over Hawks

events.name: Phoenix Suns at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — The Knicks had been forcing Devin Booker to give up the ball, and for most of the game he was fine with an open teammate taking the shot.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker hits 3-pointer with 1.7 seconds left, Suns beat Knicks 116-113 for 7th straight win

headlines.description: — Franz Wagner and Cole Anthony scored 30 points each to help the Orlando Magic pull away for a 130-117 victory over the Charlotte Hornets on Sunday night and extend their win streak to seven games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Franz Wagner, Cole Anthony score 30 each, Magic beat Hornets 130-117 for 7th straight win

headlines.description: — Anthony Edwards scored 24 points, Karl-Anthony Towns and Mike Conley each had 18 and the Minnesota Timberwolves routed the Memphis Grizzlies 119-97 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anthony Edwards scores 24 points, Timberwolves rout Grizzlies 119-97

headlines.description: — Spencer Dinwiddie scored 24 points and the Brooklyn Nets made an NBA season-best 25 3-pointers in a 118-109 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets hit NBA season-high 25 3-pointers, beat Bulls 118-106

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had 24 points and eight assists and Max Strus scored his 20 points in the third quarter, helping the Cleveland Cavaliers to a 105-102 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 24 points as the Cavaliers defeat the Raptors 105-102

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had a season-high 39 points to go with 11 rebounds and nine assists, and the Nuggets spoiled the Denver debut of Victor Wembanyama with a 132-120 win over San Antonio on Sunday night, sending the Spurs to their 12th straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic has near triple-double, leads Nuggets over Spurs, 132-120
